Talking from Sleep
Some kids talk at night.
I don't mean the ones who wake up and tell us something that happened the day before, but the children who talk while they sleep.
When it happens for the first time, it may startle you, but it's actually meaningless.
It is a harmless sleep disorder called somniocovina.
It is quite common, especially in children and adolescents.
I'm sure you told many of you that he was talking at night from sleep.
This phenomenon can occur very sporadically (for example, once in a lifetime of high fevers), or with greater regularity (every day, once a week, once every month...), the next day the baby does not remember anything.
There is only one reason to explain her onset.
It is often associated with other sleep disorders, such as nightmares, nighttime fury, enuresis nocturna (night bedwetting) or sleepwalking, but this may not be the case.
As mentioned earlier, it can often accompany very high fevers, stressful or excitable situations.
In any case, it is a little-explored phenomenon.
The intensity with which it appears is also different.
The child can speak in a calm voice, say individual words, whisper, or vice versa (crying, crying, long speeches...).
In cases where he manifests himself with great strength, it would be advisable to observe the child and consult a specialist to see if he has any problem that causes him a great deal of anxiety and manifests himself in this way.
We said it is a harmless disorder, so it is not treated only if it is associated with another sleep disorder that can be treated (for example, if it is associated with apnea syndrome or with permanent stress).
However, we can do that we will keep in mind a few very simple preventive measures, such as:
Trying not to upset the baby too much before going to sleep.
So to look for quiet games and avoid scary or rather violent TV programs or series.
For very nervous children and those who can work to relax, it is possible to use relaxation techniques that will help them to gain a certain inner peace.
This will allow the child to sleep more peacefully.
When somniocovina appears, try to remain calm.
Remind yourself that it is harmless to the child and that from what was happening, the next day he will no longer remember anything.
Useful advice
Don't be him.
It is useless because it is not conscious and you will interrupt his sleep.
Even when he speaks, he sleeps, and therefore rests.
